race.comment: THE IRISH (4) may have suffered from the dreaded second-up syndrome at the latest effort but the form prior was full of merit. Gets in well after the claim and expecting a big bounce back. SAN GABRIEL (7) has been thereabouts in recent outings and rarely puts in a poor one. Rates well in this line up and has drawn to get every chance. MANNERHEIM gets a key switch with Maloney going aboard and he should be strong late. LOYALTY COUNTS (10) was a nice winner last start and appears capable of going back to back.
